From ce3deb3800574ff8ad5c1c083cdf1e51003b809f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 13:44:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(slayzone): extension-capable inline tabs via windowless
 per-task Browser
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Embedded browser panes now back onto real tabs in a windowless per-task
Browser (was bare WebContents::Create), so tabs are chrome.tabs-addressable
and get TabHelpers — the foundation for extensions (1Password) and per-task
profiles. Each task = its own windowId; the Browser never shows an OS window
but still registers in BrowserList/WindowControllerList.

Five fixes to render + navigate without fighting the takeover shell:
- tag helper Browsers via user_title (kEmbeddedTabBrowserMarker) so the
  window factory gives them a plain BrowserView, not SlayzoneBrowserView —
  else each loads chrome://slayzone-shell, opens a pane, and recurses
- IncrementCapturerCount keepalive: a tab in a never-shown Browser is
  marked hidden and produces no frames
- park a dummy active about:blank tab so content tabs stay background — a
  BrowserView owns its active tab's RWHV (trapped in the hidden window)
- NON-idempotent CreateView: the renderer remounts its NativeAnchor, and a
  shared view_id let the old anchor's teardown destroy the live tab
- re-attach the slot on PrimaryPageChanged so cross-origin render-view
  swaps actually repaint (URL updated but page was frozen otherwise)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
